<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCP/comments/9mkms3/hi_this_should_be_the_first_iteration_of_the/?utm_content=title&amp;utm_medium=new&amp;utm_source=reddit&amp;utm_name=SCP">SCP-173 Original 4chan post</a> - This cropped up on reddit this month and caused a bit of a stir, with good reason. As it implies, this is the closest thing we have to original 4chan thread for SCP-173 and some of the other objects. Check it out!</li>
<li><a href="/and-then-i-died-series-2">And Then I Died IV - Series 2</a> - Shaggydredlocks restarted this old game! The premise is simple: someone writes a small entry ending with 'and then I died' featuring a single SCP and you guess what SCP did the killing! If you guess correctly, then it's your turn to write an entry. We're eleven entries in so far and this last one seems to be quite the head scratcher. Go and give it a go!</li>
<li><a href="/scp-international">SCP International</a> - The International Wiki has teamed up with us to post some of their best articles over the month of October, with the last being posted in November! They have a hub but we've also made a collection of the articles posted at the bottom of this page. Go check it out!</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2232">SCP-2232</a> (&quot;Birdphone. Think Different.&quot;), by minmin, a quick look at Birdphone!™ the next logical step following carrier pigeons.</li>
<li><a href="/CryogenChaos-Comment-Tales">CryogenChaos' Comment Tales</a>, by, you guessed it, CryogenChaos, A collection of neat gems hidden in the comments of other SCPs.</li>
<li>In <a href="/the-dark-web-dke79-o2rg5-4jlw6">'The Dark Web' (DKE79/O2RG5/4JLW6)</a>, by drchandra, MC&amp;D make their first venture into the wonderful world of THE CLOUD!</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Event Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>The theme for the month of October was <em>Shadow!</em></p>
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/scp-2524">SCP-2524</a> (&quot;No Strings&quot;), by tygently, a wax candle has a bit of fun with the Foundation.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-1806">SCP-1806</a> (&quot;Shadow Sculpture&quot;), by sandrewswann, we see what happens when your shadow crosses over the path of true darkness.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-1553">SCP-1553</a> (&quot;Dr. Wondertainment's Shadow Paint Play-Set!&quot;), by HammerMaiden, leave shadow puppets behind with shadow paint! (Note: may cause fatigue, vomiting, and fading into the void.)</li>
</ul>
